P = (p_1,p_2, \cdots, p_n)
\sum p_i = 1
p_i  \geq 0
Q = (q_1,q_2, \cdots, q_n)
P
I^2 + Z^2 \leq 1
n=2
p=(x,1-x)
q=(1-x,x)
Z=2\sqrt{x(1-x)}
\ell(x)=\log((1-x)/x)
\ell(x)>2
x\le\frac19
I^2+Z^2>1
 2I=x\log(x/(1-x))+(1-x)\log((1-x)/x)=(1-2x)\ell(x), 
 I^2+Z^2-1=\frac14(1-2x)^2\ell(x)^2+4x(1-x)-1=\frac14(1-2x)^2(\ell(x)^2-4). 
